  "text": "watch deep options incorrect action\n\n### Vue version\r\n\r\n3.5.6\r\n\r\n### Link to minimal reproduction\r\n\r\nno\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n1.case1\r\n```js\r\nwatch(\r\n        [\r\n          () => obj.value.number,\r\n        ],\r\n        () => {\r\n          console.log('trigger')\r\n        }\r\n      );\r\n```\r\n2.case2\r\n```js\r\nwatch(\r\n        [\r\n          () => obj.value.number,\r\n        ],\r\n        () => {\r\n          console.log('trigger')\r\n        }, {\r\n          deep: true\r\n       }\r\n      );\r\n```\r\nwhen use deep: true; number no change but other prop of obj change   trigger still (Verified not to trigger when other change)\r\n\r\n### What is expected?\r\n\r\nConsistent behavior\r\n\r\n### What is actually happening?\r\n\r\nno Consistent behavior\r\n\r\n### System Info\r\n\r\n```shell\r\nChrome 128.0.6613.137\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n### Any additional comments?\r\n\r\n_No response_",
